<h2 id="40">4. Managing catalogues</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong> menu becomes visible in the plentymarkets back end once you deploy a plugin that makes catalogue templates available. Use this menu to create, edit or delete catalogues.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="50">4.1. Creating a catalogue</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to create a catalogue.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a catalogue:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong>.<br>
→ The catalogue overview opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create catalogue</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name for the catalogue.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a catalogue template from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The catalogue is created.<br>
→ The catalogue is opened for editing.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="60">4.2. Mapping data sources</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once you created a catalogue, the catalogue opens. On the left, the sales channel’s data is shown. Fields with an asterisk are mandatory. Further on the right of each data field is a drop-down list. Use these drop-down lists to map one or more plentymarkets data sources to the data fields of the sales channel.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Depending on the product data you want to transfer, you either map a data field or a value. In the upper area, you can map data fields. For example, you select which data field in plentymarkets contains the weight of variations. In the lower section, you can map values. For example, you map the sales channel’s category “Pet food” to your plentymarkets category “Animal food”.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to map the data fields of the sales channel to a plentymarkets data source.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Mapping data sources:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong>.<br>
→ The catalogue overview opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the catalogue.<br>
→ The catalogue opens.<br>
→ On the left, the sales channel’s data fields are displayed.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> Fields with an asterisk are mandatory.<br>
→ In the middle, drop-down lists with plentymarkets data sources are displayed.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>From the drop-down list, select a plentymarkets source for the data fields of the sales channel.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> Check the information in the user guide of the sales channel’s plugin for details on the target data fields. <a href="#table-catalogue-fields">Table 3</a> contains information regarding the plentymarkets data sources and how to map these data sources.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>To map another plentymarkets source to a data field, click on <strong>Add source</strong> on the right.<br>
→ A new line is added.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> Even if you map more than one data source to a data field, only one value is transferred to the sales channel. The data is checked in the order in which they were mapped. So if the first data field does not contain a value, the second data field is transmitted, etc.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Map all data you want to send to the sales channel.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The mappings are saved.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
