<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="70">4.3. Combining data sources</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For exporting data fields you can now use Own values in order to combine as many data sources as you like. To do so, create <strong>Additional sources</strong> and select a separator for each combination.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Combining data sources:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong>.<br>
→ The catalogue overview opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on a catalogue.<br>
→ The catalogue opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the line of the data field you want to export, select a plentymarkets source from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Underneath the source that you want to combine, click on <strong>Additional source</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ Another source is added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>From the left drop-down list, select <strong>Own value</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the field <strong>Value</strong>, enter the separator that you want to place between the sources.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Underneath the Own value, click on <strong>Additional source</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ Another source is added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>From the drop-down list, select a plentymarkets source that you want to combine with the first source.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If required, select further additional sources and separators via the own value. Between two sources, there always has to be a separator.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Save</strong>.<br>
→ The sources are combined and displayed with the respectively selected separator.<br>
<strong><em>Note</em></strong>: In case there is a block of data sources that does not contain any sources, this block is skipped and the next source that contains a value is used.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="90">4.4. Deleting a catalogue</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to delete a catalogue.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a catalogue:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong>.<br>
→ The catalogue overview opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the catalogue.<br>
→ The catalogue opens.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the upper right corner, click on <strong>Delete</strong> (<span class="icon red"><i class="fa fa-minus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ You are asked to confirm your decision.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Confirm the deletion.<br>
→ The catalogue is deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
